But he refused to provide enough information to authorities to arrange his deportation to Somalia, blocking his deportation again.
As of a Homeland Security inspector general’s review, he’d been in custody four years.
“We give them too many bites at the apple,” said Jessica Vaughan, an expert at the Center for Immigration Studies, who reviewed the inspector general’s report.
The migrant lost at the circuit court, ICE moved the person to a staging location in preparation for deportation.
As of the inspector general’s review the migrant had been detained for more than three years, at a cost of more than $36,000 per year.